 political practice and rethinking organizational questions that have vexed contemporary anti-capitalist movements.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aOccupy movement. 0aProtest campsxEnvironmental aspects. 0aProtest movements. 0aSalvage (Waste, etc.)xPolitical aspects. 0aSalvage (Waste, etc.)xSocial aspects. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 4aSociology : Social Movements. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2022z978311149185140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849121940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438491219423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438491219/original  a978-3-11-149185-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles